# Web Performance & SEO

Follow patterns from `Sample-temp-web-site`. Optimize for Google Core Web Vitals on every UI change.

## LCP (Largest Contentful Paint)

- Preload the LCP image in `index.html` (`rel="preload" as="image" fetchpriority="high"`).
- Above-the-fold images: explicit `width` + `height`, `fetchPriority="high"`, avoid lazy-load.
- Prefer local `/public` assets or optimized CDN URLs — not unoptimized multi-MB originals.
- Hero/logo URLs in `index.html` preload must match `IMAGES` constants exactly.

## CLS (Cumulative Layout Shift)

- Always set `width` and `height` on `<img>` (or CSS aspect-ratio) before load.
- Reserve space for fonts (`font-display: swap` on Kodchasan and FA subset).
- No layout-shifting embeds without fixed aspect-ratio containers.
- Avoid injecting content above existing UI after paint.

## Fonts & icons

- **No** `@fortawesome/*` or `react-icons` packages.
- Kodchasan via Google Fonts with `preconnect` + `display=swap`.
- Icons: custom FA subset in `src/app/utils/icons.ts` via `loadFontAwesome()` — only icons we use.
- Preload FA woff2 files in `index.html` (solid + brands).

## JS & routing

- Lazy-load route pages with `React.lazy` + `Suspense`.
- Keep initial bundle small; defer non-critical scripts.

## Images

- Centralize paths in `src/constants/images.ts`.
- Below-the-fold: `loading="lazy"` + `decoding="async"`.
- Use appropriately sized files (header logo ≠ full OG image).

## SEO

- Use `useSEO()` on every page; keep meta/canonical/OG in sync with `index.html` defaults.
- JSON-LD when page content is ready — stub until then.
